      <hedline>
        <hl1>Misplaced Grief in Syria</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Avrom Jacobs letter holds it is hard to fathom Syrian grief over death of Pres Hafez al-Assad because Assad killed thousands of his countrymen while leaving their economy most backward in region</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Syrians Bury Only Leader Many of Them Ever Knew'' (news article, June 14):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Syrians Bury Only Leader Many of Them Ever Knew'' (news article, June 14):</p>
        <p>It is hard to fathom Syrian grief over the death of President Hafez al-Assad. He may have brought electricity to farms and stabilized his rule, but he also killed thousands of his countrymen while leaving their economy the most backward in the region.</p>
        <p>Perhaps the Syrians' grief so directly reflects his brutal influence over their daily lives that they can't see him for what he really was.</p>
        <p>AVROM JACOBS  Kochav Yair, Israel, June 14, 2000</p>
      </block>
